records.addlTxt:
Defendant Mairceon V Ray in court with attorney Eryn M Menden.  Kelly Pingel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts #2, 3, 4 and 5 are dismissed and read into Count #1.    The Defendant was given the following:

Count #1:

WITHHELD SENTENCE;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS; (may be transferred to Milwaukee County).

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
*Perform 75 Hours Community Service.

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be returned to the poster);

CONDITION TIME: 30 DAYS, non working hours with standard release conditions including work and treatment. (apply 18 days credit. Defendant to report to the Huber Facility by 6:00 p.m.on Monday, June 20, 2016.) 
 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

  Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.
